    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Battery Runtime Formula</h2>
      <p>
        Runtime (hours) = <strong>battery kWh × 1000 × depth of discharge × inverter efficiency ÷ load watts</strong>. A 13.5 kWh Tesla Powerwall at 1,000 W load, 100% usable DoD, 92% inverter efficiency gives 13.5 × 1000 × 1.0 × 0.92 / 1000 = 12.42 hours. The key insight: nameplate kWh is not what you can use. Real-world runtime depends on usable fraction and inverter losses.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Typical Battery Capacities</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600">
